cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

This paper is primarily focused on computer vision, specifically on feature learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also discusses the use of egomotion as a supervisory signal, which is related to robotics and control, making cs.RO (Robotics) the second most likely sub-category. The paper also uses neural networks for feature learning, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Finally, the paper discusses the comparison of features learned using different forms of supervision, which is related to optimization and training of neural networks, making cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) a likely sub-category as well.
